  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Semite</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>Bleistein is identified as a Semite.\n        Since Jews were always so independent of nation, having\n        none of their own, they have been recognisable throughout\n        much of the history of time and were never afraid to\n        settle in new countries, often without losing their own\n        identity and tradition. Thus Bleistein, as a Semite, has\n        a better sense of the past than Burbank and remembers\n        Venice's uglier, less Romantic sides.</font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Burbank and anti-Semitism</td>\n<td><a href=\"Purgatory_I_DA.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>The City and the Stranger</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bleistein and Misrepresentation</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Burbank and Bleistein</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\"</font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Semite Bleistein is identified as a Semite. Since Jews were always so independent of nation, having none of their own, they have been recognisable throughout much of the history of time and were never afraid to settle in new countries, often without losing their own identity and tradition. Thus Bleistein, as a Semite, has a better sense of the past than Burbank and remembers Venice's uglier, less Romantic sides. reference topics Burbank and anti-Semitism The City and the Stranger Bleistein and Misrepresentation Burbank and Bleistein back to \"Burbank\"",
